ers/seanmonstar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/seanmonstar/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"event":"renamed","commit_id":null,"commit_url":null,"created_at":"2022-05-18T23:52:32Z","rename":{"from":"Hyper does not open the customization of the max_header_list_size method in the H2 third-party software. As a result, HTTP2 attacks may occur when Hyper is used.","to":"Allow specifying the HTTP/2 SETTINGS_MAX_HEADER_LIST_SIZE"},"performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/hyper/issues/comments/1441527098","html_url":"https://github.com/hyperium/hyper/issues/2826#issuecomment-1441527098","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/hyper/issues/2826","id":1441527098,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAWaYQc5V6_U6","user":{"login":"JanZerebecki","id":7452727,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc0NTI3Mjc=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7452727?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/JanZerebecki","html_url":"https://github.com/JanZerebecki","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JanZerebecki/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JanZerebecki/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JanZerebecki/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JanZerebecki/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JanZerebecki/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JanZerebecki/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JanZerebecki/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JanZerebecki/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JanZerebecki/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2023-02-23T10:33:46Z","updated_at":"2023-02-23T10:33:46Z","body":"Note, the client is vulnerable to this, too, but is not yet fixed.\r\n\r\nI don't currently have a need for it being fixed, just wanted to document it, as discussion elsewhere was confused about this:\r\n\r\nBoth directions of HTTP have headers, v2 specs the related advisory setting for both directions. The underlying h2 does have this setting for both client and server since almost its beginning, which comes with a default limit of 16MB.\r\n\r\nFor this to be a problem the application does need to have some thing else going on whose denial of service by memory exhaustion would be a problem. This something else might be requests to other servers that are not in the same security compartment. Or having taken a lock that needs to be released. Or it might be even a totally unrelated thing, like showing a GUI. Based on the 16MB default and the maximum outstanding in flight requests and the available memory you can calculate if this can be a problem. So a CLI application that just one command, which does one request, then exits anyway and is prepared to be killed at any time (instead of needing to avoid allocation failures) doesn't need this setting.","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/hyper/issues/comments/1441527098/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"JanZerebecki","id":7452727,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc0NTI3Mjc=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7452727?v=4","gravatar_id":""